    "finalText": "Here’s where your current project intelligence stands, as of 2026-05-14:\n\n**Source Sync Health**\n- **Teams:** One critical Teams DM export (acannon@alleatogroup.com) is currently flagged as critical — that means messages from this user’s DMs may be missing from searches. All other Teams channels appear operational, but if you’re looking for high-stakes, recent DMs with acannon, results may be incomplete.\n- **Outlook:** Outlook sync is partially degraded. Critical mailboxes with failed/critical status: njepson@alleatogroup.com, mparsons@alleatogroup.com, mharrison@alleatogroup.com, jdawson@alleatogroup.com, ctragesser@alleatogroup.com. This impacts the ability to reliably search for recent, sent, or received messages for these users. Other mailboxes should be intact.\n- **Meetings:** No system-level errors are flagged for meeting transcript retrieval, but meeting intelligence packets depend on source compilation. With a current reported backlog of 11,501 uncompiled items, there’s a significant lag between raw meeting recordings and readout availability. The most recent meetings may not be fully reflected in rollups or summaries.\n- **Intelligence Packets:** 1,065 unembedded sources means there’s a coverage gap for vector-based/semantic search, which affects the completeness and freshness of AI-generated packet summaries and cross-project trends.\n\n**What’s Stale/Missing Right Now**\n- **New emails and Teams DMs for flagged users may not show up in searches or readouts until sync issues are resolved.**\n- **Recent meetings may not be included in project packets**, especially if they happened in the last few days and haven’t cleared the embedding/compiling pipeline.\n- **AI summaries and rollups (including project “health” packets) are lagging behind real time**. Fast-moving issues or recent owner decisions may NOT be in the latest packets shown in chat.\n- **General task and document signals are likely up to date**, but any finding tied specifically to a flagged mailbox, DM, or very recent meeting may be incomplete.\n\n**Bottom Line**\nRely on current AI readouts for portfolio-wide and historic trend analysis. For time-sensitive issues (this week’s decisions, urgent owner asks, anything involving the flagged mailboxes or acannon’s Teams DMs), double-check raw communications or request a direct lookup. If you’re about to make a financial or operational decision based on the readout, ask if there’s an uncompiled meeting, email, or packet update covering that event, especially if it’s within the last week.\n\n**Next Step**\n- If you name a specific project, person, or timeframe, I can check what the most recent compiled sources actually cover and flag exactly what’s real-time and what’s at risk of staleness. \n- For any decision under tight time pressure, cross-verify against direct mailbox, Teams, or meeting export if critical.\n\nIf you need a QC on a specific project’s signals or a named person’s communications, tell me who/what to check and I’ll audit for gaps."
